Answer Click to reveal the answer. Do some algebra and confirm $f^{-1} = x^2 + 1$. Note Because the range of $f$ is $[0, \infty)$, the domain of $f^{-1}$ is only $[0,\infty)$, meaning it&rsquo;s only the right-half of the parabola! (otherwise it&rsquo;s not one-to-one).
